Its precise date is not of importance for our purpose. We would gladly know more of the original from which it was copied. That original contained (probably seven times) an abbreviation sor Nam (see below), which the scribe of A did not understand. It probably contained the square forms of the spiritus asper (t) in lines 188, 305, 407, and of the spiritus lenis (⁴) in line 5451. It made possible the confusion between n and r (line 161 and perhaps line 243); between r and s (496 and perhaps 128 and 458); in line 23 the omission of the fourth letter in plasmazcerz't may be due to the same cause.
